==English==
===Noun phrase===
'''[[mandarin]] [[orange]]''' (''plural'' '''mandarin oranges''')

#(''also'' '''mandarin''') A small citrus tree (''Citrus reticulata'') with fruit resembling the [[orange]].
#(''also'' '''mandarin''') The fruit of this tree, smaller than an orange and [[oblate]].

====Synonyms====
*[[tangerine]]

====Alternate spelling====
*[[mandarine]] [[orange]]

